body:
It's all here, support both Kafka9 and Kafka10. I tried option2, option3, and decide to submit option3 which is lightweight, and transparent. 
1). the steps to call SpEL happen during start(), not a big concern about performance;
2). the differences of API input List/Collection/Varargs can be handled by SpEL, so actually there's no special code for either Kafka9 or Kafka10;

Now we'll continue with one Kafka IO module, using Kafka client 0.9 by default, which can work with Kafka0.9 and 0.10. 

As the note added in KafkaIO JavaDoc, `It's supported to replace with Kafka client 0.10 for external authentication.`, simply by exclude Kafka client in Kafka IO module, and add Kafka client 0.10. -- I should add the full words there.

@XuMingmin, nice! 
Can you change kafka-client dependency to [9.0.1, 11)? That way it will pick up the latest release or the one explicitly included by the users. It will also ensure that our builds succeed with Kafka 0.10.x.

This also implies users can have their own Consumer implementation (if they need to) and spring will handle it correctly, right?
